An introduction to concepts, approaches and theories of clinical psychology. The course gives general framework for psychological explanations of development of disorders and interventions. Several disorders and therapies will be explained in detail at lectures, students are expected to go through independently the rest by textbook.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To teach ability to distinguish evidence-based approach to mental disorders from conventional thinking.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Is familiar with basic principles and concepts of clinical psychology. Knows psychological models of mental and behavioural disorders. Is familiar with main therapeutic approaches. Knows ethical priciples of psychologists.
